---
import MarketingLayout from "~/layouts/MarketingLayout.astro";
const canonical = new URL("/mounts/", Astro.site).toString();
---
<MarketingLayout title="TV Wall Mount Guidance | Melbourne TVs" description="Fixed, tilt and full-motion TV bracket selection is confirmed against the television, wall, load and room layout." canonical={canonical} ogImage="https://cdn.brisbanetvs.com/work/v1/tv-wall-bracket.jpg">
  <article class="simple"><p class="eyebrow">Bracket selection</p><h1>The right movement and load rating come first.</h1><p>Bracket recommendations are included with a scoped quote. We check the TV weight and VESA pattern, wall construction, viewing angle, desired extension and access before proposing a mount.</p><a href="/quote/">Send the TV and wall details →</a></article>
</MarketingLayout>
<style>.simple{width:min(850px,calc(100% - 40px));margin:90px auto 120px}.simple h1{font-size:clamp(2.5rem,6vw,5rem);line-height:1.05}.simple p{font-size:1.15rem;color:#52615b}.simple a{display:inline-block;margin-top:20px;font-weight:700}.eyebrow{text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.12em;font-size:.76rem!important;color:#247253!important;font-weight:700}</style>
